To set the font size on a multilineedit widget in Fyne, you can use the following code:

```
import (
    "fyne.io/fyne/v2"
    "fyne.io/fyne/v2/widget"
)

func main() {
    // create a new multilineedit widget
    mle := widget.NewMultiLineEntry()

    // set the font size to 18 points
    mle.SetTextSize(18)

    // set the widget size
    mle.Resize(fyne.NewSize(200, 200))

    // create a new window
    w := fyne.NewWindow("MultilineEdit Widget")

    // set the widget as the content of the window
    w.SetContent(mle)

    // show the window
    w.ShowAndRun()
}
```

In this code, we first create a new multilineedit widget using the `widget.NewMultiLineEntry()` function. We then use the `SetTextSize()` method to set the font size to 18 points. Finally, we set the size of the widget and add it to a new window using the `fyne.NewWindow()` and `w.SetContent()` functions, respectively. Once everything is set up, we show the window using the `w.ShowAndRun()` function.
